Package chess

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FirstTurnAfterMove
    Used in pawns to unset them after their opponent has made a move.
    HasMoved
    Used for pieces which care about whether they have moved or not (like king, pawn, and rook).
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Bishop
    Implementation of Piece class representing the bishop.
    Board
    Board holds the pieces and their state.
    ChessOld
    Main entry function for our program.
    InputParser
    InputParser parses the input and interacts with Board as needed
    King
    Implementation of Piece class representing the king.
    Knight
    Implementation of Piece class representing the knight.
    Pawn
    Implementation of Piece class representing the pawn.
    Piece
    Piece is an abstract class that holds all the data types shared by all chess pieces.
    Piece.Coords
    Used for returning pairs of locations (r, c).
    Queen
    Implementation of Piece class representing the queen.
    Rook
    Implementation of Piece class representing the rook.
